Share Quick Text Using a Folder in Lightning Experience

Use folders to create unique sets of quick text messages for different business units. Create separate folders for each division and share them with users in that division.

Available in: Lightning Experience, Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions.

To create a quick text folder: 
Create on quick text
To share a quick text folder: 
Owner of the folder OR Manage access on the folder
To manage and share all quick text folders: 
View Setup and Configurations AND Modify All on quick text

You can create up to four levels of folders. When a user shares a folder, all messages in the folder are shared.

Sharing settings on folders override sharing settings on individual quick text messages.

On the Quick Text Settings page in Setup, select Share and organize quick text in folders.

Organize your quick text into folders to be shared with other users.
From the App Launcher, select Quick Text to open the Quick text tab.
In the quick text folder list view, select All Folders, Created by Me, or Shared with Me to review the folders you have access to.
Click the dropdown menu next to a folder in the list, and select Share.

Enter the sharing details. You can share with users, groups, roles, or other groupings using a combination.

Click Share.

You can also use the Analytics Folder API to create and manage folders.
title: Share and Organize Quick Text in Service Cloud
